00:08:52.700 --> 00:08:55.925
So select the frame, click Background,

00:08:55.925 --> 00:08:59.765
and then sample the very last color pixel of the image.

00:08:59.765 --> 00:09:04.130
Zoom in real close to get a better handle and pay attention to the pixels from here,

00:09:04.130 --> 00:09:07.760
this shows which pixel will be sampled exactly simple,

00:09:07.760 --> 00:09:09.995
that lighter pixel that is next to the edge.

00:09:09.995 --> 00:09:13.340
The reason why we are selecting the last pixel is to create

00:09:13.340 --> 00:09:15.950
a smooth transition as possible between

00:09:15.950 --> 00:09:19.055
